Generic single-database configuration.

## Migration chain (Alembic — FSMA schema)

The Alembic migrations in `alembic/versions/` manage the **FSMA-specific schema
only**. The current revision chain is:

  a1b2c3d4e5f6  (baseline — V042, consolidates V002–V042)
       ↓
  b2c3d4e5f6a7  V048 — operational hardening (SLA tracking, chain verification log)
       ↓
  c3d4e5f6a7b8  V049 — fsma_audit_trail persistent log
       ↓
  d4e5f6a7b8c9  V050 — task_queue (replaces Kafka consumers)
       ↓
  e5f6a7b8c9d0  V051 — RLS for 8 V042 tenant_* tables + consolidated SQL RLS hardening
                        (SQL_V048 sysadmin defense-in-depth, SQL_V049 obligations/FTL,
                         SQL_V050 reference tables)

To upgrade to the latest head:

    alembic upgrade head

## Admin service migrations (separate runner)

`services/admin/migrations/V1–V36` are managed **outside Alembic** by the
admin service's own migration runner (Flyway / raw SQL). They must be applied
manually or via the admin service startup process. Do **not** attempt to run
them with `alembic upgrade` — they are not registered in `alembic_version`.

The Alembic chain covers the FSMA-specific schema (`fsma.*`) only. The admin
service migrations cover the `public` schema tables managed by the admin
service (tenants, memberships, users, API keys, etc.).

## Conflicting SQL file names

The `migrations/` directory contains SQL files prefixed `SQL_V048`, `SQL_V049`,
and `SQL_V050`. These were originally named `V048`, `V049`, `V050` and
conflicted with the Alembic migrations of the same numbers. They have been
renamed with the `SQL_` prefix to avoid confusion. Their content has been
incorporated into the V051 Alembic migration (`upgrade()` function) so they
are applied as part of the normal `alembic upgrade head` flow.
